      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A July 2 letter writer, commenting on the map of the human genetic code, suggests that we ''try to find the code for a more effective education system or to eliminate starvation and poverty.''</p>
        <p>Finding and putting such a code into effect would obviously be a great boon to humanity. But finding it might well raise questions about patenting it and to whom the patent might be sold -- venture capitalists, governments, politicians or writers?</p>
        <p>LEONARD D. HARRIS  Ossining, N.Y., July 2, 2000</p>
      </block>
